@Node "Design_DANGER"
@Title "D A N G E R   ! ! !
@TOC "Design"

                          D A N G E R    ! ! !

  Using the items in this menu can have very sad consequences, so make
a backup of the CharData directory before you change anything.

  As a general rule you should look at some examples before you try
designing on your own. Specificly you should keep in mind that:

o A race should have at least one class allowed.

o If a class can cast priest spells you must make a priesthood
  available to it, even if the class is not a priest (e.g. Paladins
  and Rangers).

o If a class can cast wizard spells you must make a wizard school
  available to it, even if the class is not a wizard (e.g. Bards).

  When you create new things by using this menu you may get the
message: 'Not room for more races !' or something similar. The cure
for this is simple (assuming you have enough memory). Save all you
work, quit the program, and start it again. You will now have some
more working space.

@Endnode

