@Node "Settings_Character_Spec.Bonus"
@Title "Settings/Options/This character/Spec. bonus on missile weapons"
@TOC "Settings_Character"
@Prev "Settings_Character_Multiple"
@Next "Settings_Character_InitiativeDex"

  According to Players Handbook the +1 to hit and +2 on damage given
to weapon specialists only apply to meele weapons. This option allows
you to also gain these bonuses on missile weapons.

@Endnode

@Node "Settings_Character_InitiativeDex"
@Title "Settings/Options/This character/Initiative adjusted by dex."
@TOC "Settings_Character"
@Prev "Settings_Character_Spec.Bonus"
@Next "Settings_Character_InitiativeArmor"

  This is a rule I use myself. The speed of weapons are adjusted by
dexterity reaction adjustment. Thus a character with 17 dex gains a +2
bonus on initiative when fighting (see the effect on weapon speed).

@Endnode

@Node "Settings_Character_InitiativeArmor"
@Title "Settings/Options/This character/Initiative adjusted by armor"
@TOC "Settings_Character"
@Prev "Settings_Character_InitiativeDex"
@Next "Settings_Character_ExcepStr"

  This is a rule I use myself. Uses the dex check penalty for armor
(from Fighter's Handbook) as a penalty on initiative. This penalty can
be reduced by magical armor (each '+' reduces the penalty by one,
although it cannot make the penalty into a bonus). Thus if a character
wore a Banded Mail + 1 (Banded mail has a dex check penalty of -2) the
penalty for wearing armor would be -1 on initiative (see the effect on
weapon speed). Shields do not affect initiative under this rule. Use
this rule as a counterbalance to the @{" Initiative adjusted by dex. " LINK "Settings_Character_InitiativeDex"} rule.

@Endnode

@Node "Settings_Character_ExcepStr"
@Title "Settings/Options/This character/All races can have Excep Str"
@TOC "Settings_Character"
@Prev "Settings_Character_InitiativeArmor"
@Next "Settings_Character_Int"

